        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 9 at 3:09AM CST by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>A band of lake effect snow is expected to pivot eastward around
southern Lake Michigan between daybreak and noon central time
today. As the band shifts eastward, snow rates of 1 inch per hour
may allow for snow to stick to untreated roadways as well as
bridges and overpasses. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 3 inches
are expected, though locally higher amounts cannot be ruled out.

If you encounter the band of lake effect snow, travel at safe speeds
and keep adequate distances between you and the car in front of you.

Intense lake effect snow is expected tonight and Monday. A Winter
Storm Warning goes into effect for Lake and Porter counties at 10
PM CT. A Winter Weather Advisory goes into effect for Jasper and
Newton counties at 12 AM CT. Both products will remain in effect
through 6 PM Monday.
</description>
